<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-413-627  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 413 627.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic Engineering Times  Sept 17 1990 n608 p26(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Translation-tech eyed. (machine translation) (includes relatedarticle on the 1966 Automatic Language Processing AdvisoryCommittee report and its influence)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Robinson, Brian.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>US industry and government are seriously considering supportingmachine translation technology due to the high cost of humantranslation, dropping computing costs and research and developmentbeing done in Japan.andP;  US interest in machine translation has beenscant ever since a 1966 National Research Council report deemedthe quality poor and the cost of research too high.andP;  Most majorJapanese electronics and computer companies are investing aconsiderable amount of money in the research and development ofmachine translation technology.andP;  The US Congress is debating whatsupport can be provided and machine translation is an area ofcooperation under the US/Japan Agreement for Cooperation inScience and Technology.andP;  It is believed that machine translationcan greatly help the US to access foreign technological andscientific information in the fast-growing world of technology.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Language TranslationForeign LanguagesInternational CommunicationsResearch and DevelopmentJapanese LanguageAutomation.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>